so you don't need to worry
about the boys. Thank you.

246
00:23:36,671 --> 00:23:38,506
Hey, I'm driving you
to the hospital.

247
00:23:38,508 --> 00:23:40,674
No, no, that's...

248
00:23:40,676 --> 00:23:43,209
You don't have to.
I will drive you.

249
00:23:43,211 --> 00:23:45,011
Thank you. Yeah.

250
00:23:45,013 --> 00:23:48,514
He's deteriorating rapidly. I don't
think he's gonna survive the afternoon.

251
00:23:48,516 --> 00:23:50,783
Put him in an ambulance
and take him to Houston.

252
00:23:50,785 --> 00:23:52,785
This facility isn't equipped.

253
00:23:52,787 --> 00:23:54,720
Don't you think we should
helicopter him to Hermann?

254
00:23:54,722 --> 00:23:57,083
No. Nobody's flying
in this weather.

255
00:23:57,757 --> 00:24:01,259
<i>As my condition was</i>
<i>deteriorating rapidly,</i>

256
00:24:01,261 --> 00:24:03,061
<i>it was decided</i>
<i>to move me by ambulance</i>

257
00:24:03,063 --> 00:24:06,697
<i>for the 80-mile trip back</i>
<i>to Houston's Hermann Hospital</i>

258
00:24:06,699 --> 00:24:09,100
<i>which had</i>
<i>a much better trauma center.</i>

259
00:24:09,102 --> 00:24:13,103
<i>Still, I kept wondering</i>
<i>why God had brought me back.</i>

260
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:16,706
Ah, hey,
you gotta do something.

261
00:24:16,708 --> 00:24:18,541
You gotta...

262
00:24:18,543 --> 00:24:20,911
Medicine, plea... You gotta
give me some medicine.

263
00:24:20,913 --> 00:24:24,214
- I've given you all I can.
- No, you gotta give me more.

264
00:24:43,736 --> 00:24:46,004
Ma'am, my name is Eva Piper.

265
00:24:46,006 --> 00:24:48,072
Has my husband,
Donald Piper, arrived?

266
00:24:48,074 --> 00:24:50,275
- He's in transit and should be here any moment.
- He's not here yet?

267
00:24:50,277 --> 00:24:53,237
No. He'll be coming in from
over there when he does.

268
00:24:54,779 --> 00:24:58,982
Don? Don? I'm here. They're
gonna take good care of you.

269
00:24:58,984 --> 00:25:00,917
Listen to me.

270
00:25:00,919 --> 00:25:03,420
It wasn't your fault.
You're gonna make it.

271
00:25:03,422 --> 00:25:05,462
Ma'am, we've gotta go.
You're gonna make it.

272
00:25:08,659 --> 00:25:11,293
We need you to fill out
these insurance forms.

273
00:25:11,295 --> 00:25:13,495
Thank you.

274
00:25:21,705 --> 00:25:25,441
I know, uh,
Don's date of birth.

275
00:25:25,443 --> 00:25:28,044
I don't know his
social security number

276
00:25:28,046 --> 00:25:29,979
or his insurance company.

277
00:25:29,981 --> 00:25:34,150
I don't know the amount
of the deductible.

278
00:25:34,152 --> 00:25:37,653
Don's always taken care of this. I don't
have the answers... It's okay. It's okay.

279
00:25:37,655 --> 00:25:40,496
These are the easy
questions for now.

280
00:25:41,224 --> 00:25:44,794
All I know is that Don is supposed
to lead evening services.

281
00:25:44,796 --> 00:25:46,862
He's meant to preach tonight.

282
00:25:46,864 --> 00:25:49,025
They already have that covered.

283
00:25:50,700 --> 00:25:52,901
I don't know any of this.

284
00:25:52,903 --> 00:25:55,136
Ma'am, I filled out
what I could,

285
00:25:55,138 --> 00:25:56,905
but I don't... I don't have
his information.

286
00:25:56,907 --> 00:25:58,706
I'll get it to you tomorrow.
That's okay.

287
00:25:58,708 --> 00:26:01,208
We deal with this situation every day.
Thank you.

288
00:26:10,019 --> 00:26:12,920
Oh. <i>It was heartwarming</i>

289
00:26:12,922 --> 00:26:16,357
<i>to know Eva had the support of our
friends and fellow church members</i>

290
00:26:16,359 --> 00:26:18,892
<i>in her hour of need.</i>

291
00:26:25,902 --> 00:26:28,837
<i>Surgeon Kelly,</i>
<i>please report to Room 25.</i>

292
00:26:28,839 --> 00:26:31,272
It's been over an hour.

293
00:26:31,274 --> 00:26:34,755
I can't stand the
tension of not knowing.

294
00:26:35,944 --> 00:26:38,212
I'm gonna find out what's happening.
Eva, Eva.

295
00:26:38,214 --> 00:26:39,780
I need answers.

296
00:26:43,885 --> 00:26:45,518
Doctor? May I help you?

297
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:48,854
I'm trying to find out what's going
on with my husband, Donald Piper.

298
00:26:48,856 --> 00:26:50,356
No one's been out
to see you yet?

299
00:26:50,358 --> 00:26:53,625
No, no one. I've heard nothing.
I'm so sorry.

300
00:26:53,627 --> 00:26:57,363
I'm Tom Greider, the
orthopedic surgeon on this.

301
00:26:57,365 --> 00:27:01,767
Um, come on and I'll show
you what's going on.

302
00:27:01,769 --> 00:27:04,436
Your husband is
very badly injured.

303
00:27:04,438 --> 00:27:07,939
We<i> are</i> doing everything
we can to save him.

304
00:27:07,941 --> 00:27:09,607
See this?

305
00:27:09,609 --> 00:27:12,810
It's not just broken.
It's shattered.

306
00:27:14,046 --> 00:27:16,547
He's missing significant
amounts of bone structure,

307
00:27:16,549 --> 00:27:18,782
muscle and skin.

308
00:27:18,784 --> 00:27:21,485
That's his right knee.

309
00:27:21,487 --> 00:27:26,991
And this is where the left thigh
bone, or femur, should be.

310
00:27:28,460 --> 00:27:30,327
Should be?

311
00:27:30,329 --> 00:27:34,231
Well, he's missing a
significant amount of bone.

312
00:27:34,233 --> 00:27:35,932
Four and a half inches.

313
00:27:35,934 --> 00:27:39,603
Also, it seems that he
has a cracked pelvis.

314
00:27:39,605 --> 00:27:43,473
But, uh, we're just gonna let
that go for the time being,

315
00:27:43,475 --> 00:27:47,010
'cause we have to deal with these
other injuries right away.

316
00:27:47,012 --> 00:27:49,245
As you can see,

317
00:27:49,247 --> 00:27:52,582
only this soft tissue at
the bottom part of his leg

318
00:27:52,584 --> 00:27:56,319
is connecting his whole lower
left leg to the rest of his body.

319
00:27:57,788 --> 00:28:00,089
Would you like to see him?

320
00:28:00,091 --> 00:28:02,192
Yes, I would.

321
00:28:02,194 --> 00:28:03,826
Well, come on.

322
00:28:07,130 --> 00:28:10,099
He won't respond to you.
He's heavily medicated.

323
00:28:13,203 --> 00:28:16,705
We couldn't give him anything until
we'd finished our examination.

324
00:28:19,508 --> 00:28:22,377
They're coming to take him
to surgery now.

325
00:29:24,513 --> 00:29:27,749
God.

326
00:29:29,518 --> 00:29:31,185
God help me.

327
00:29:35,190 --> 00:29:37,024
Please help us.

328
00:29:40,395 --> 00:29:42,295
I'm so scared.

329
00:29:46,634 --> 00:29:49,970
You've always helped us.

330
00:29:49,972 --> 00:29:52,872
Now, please...

331
00:29:52,874 --> 00:29:54,373
please help us.

332
00:30:02,483 --> 00:30:04,116
Please help us.

333
00:30:33,918 --> 00:30:36,352
For I know the plans
they have for you.

334
00:30:42,626 --> 00:30:44,894
<i>Plans to prosper you.</i>

335
00:30:47,430 --> 00:30:49,364
<i>And to not harm you.</i>

336
00:30:52,802 --> 00:30:56,772
<i>To give you hope and a future.</i>

337
00:30:56,774 --> 00:30:59,708
<i>Survival was going</i>
<i>to be difficult</i>

338
00:30:59,710 --> 00:31:03,579
<i>because heaven was so glorious.</i>

339
00:31:09,153 --> 00:31:10,552
Hi, Dad.

340
00:31:13,222 --> 00:31:14,856
Okay.

341
00:31:17,893 --> 00:31:19,561
Not good.

342
00:31:26,870 --> 00:31:28,537
I don't know.

343
00:31:29,639 --> 00:31:31,239
I don't know, Dad.

344
00:31:31,241 --> 00:31:34,376
I'll see you tomorrow
with the kids.

345
00:31:38,748 --> 00:31:40,982
<i>I just spoke to Don's parents.</i>

346
00:31:40,984 --> 00:31:44,386
<i>They aren't getting here</i>
<i>until the day after tomorrow.</i>

347
00:31:44,388 --> 00:31:47,489
<i>I love you too. Bye.</i>

348
00:31:51,862 --> 00:31:55,397
The reason you haven't heard from us
is 'cause we worked on him all night.

349
00:31:55,399 --> 00:31:58,601
- All night?
- Eleven and a half hours.

350
00:31:58,603 --> 00:32:01,103
The good news is there's
no sign of brain damage

351
00:32:01,105 --> 00:32:03,372
or internal injury.

352
00:32:03,374 --> 00:32:06,908
We stabilized his left arm and
put his left leg in traction.

353
00:32:06,910 --> 00:32:09,945
We're taking good care
of your husband, Eva.

354
00:32:09,947 --> 00:32:12,414
He's gonna be okay.

355
00:32:13,349 --> 00:32:15,317
Thank you, Doctor.

356
00:32:17,119 --> 00:32:19,888
There are a lot of people
in the hospital chapel

357
00:32:19,890 --> 00:32:22,156
praying for Don right now.

358
00:32:25,026 --> 00:32:28,329
How you doing? Okay.

359
00:32:31,967 --> 00:32:35,536
I don't want you
to think about this now, but

360
00:32:35,538 --> 00:32:38,372
you should consider
hiring an attorney.

361
00:32:44,378 --> 00:32:47,046
<i>Enduring all</i>
<i>that I had to go through,</i>

362
00:32:47,048 --> 00:32:49,449
<i>nobody put up</i>
<i>with more than Eva.</i>

363
00:32:49,451 --> 00:32:52,285
<i>She would rise</i>
<i>every morning at 6:00,</i>

364
00:32:52,287 --> 00:32:54,053
<i>rush to work at the school</i>

365
00:32:54,055 --> 00:32:55,889
<i>and afterwards</i>
<i>hurry back to my bedside,</i>

366
00:32:55,891 --> 00:32:58,791
<i>where she stayed with me</i>
<i>every night.</i>

367
00:32:58,793 --> 00:33:02,161
<i>It was the same stressful
routine day after day for her.</i>

368
00:33:03,897 --> 00:33:05,497
You're seriously injured.

369
00:33:07,233 --> 00:33:09,068
We've done an MRI on you,

370
00:33:09,070 --> 00:33:11,670
and it seems you've
escaped brain damage.

371
00:33:14,174 --> 00:33:18,376
I hurt more than I believe
is humanly possible.

372
00:33:19,277 --> 00:33:21,645
We can help you manage that.

373
00:33:23,014 --> 00:33:25,483
I just want relief.

374
00:33:26,084 --> 00:33:28,785
I understand.

375
00:33:28,787 --> 00:33:30,553
Your family's here to see you.

376
00:33:32,023 --> 00:33:34,257
<i>The hardest thing to endure</i>

377
00:33:34,259 --> 00:33:36,959
<i>was having my family,</i>
<i>especially my children,</i>

378
00:33:36,961 --> 00:33:39,662
<i>seeing me</i>
<i>in this physical state.</i>

379
00:33:40,497 --> 00:33:42,197
Don?

380
00:33:43,098 --> 00:33:45,667
It's okay, boys.
Say hi to your dad.

381
00:33:45,669 --> 00:33:47,268
Nicole.

382
00:33:57,681 --> 00:33:59,548
I love you, Daddy.

383
00:34:00,716 --> 00:34:03,918
I love you, Dad. Love you.

384
00:34:06,021 --> 00:34:08,790
I love you, Chris,

385
00:34:08,792 --> 00:34:11,258
so much.

386
00:34:14,129 --> 00:34:17,898
I have a Valentine's
Day dance coming up.

387
00:34:17,900 --> 00:34:19,967
I'm very excited.

388
00:34:19,969 --> 00:34:23,035
Although I don't know
if I have a Valentine.

389
00:34:25,038 --> 00:34:28,207
Daddy will dance with you.

390
00:34:28,209 --> 00:34:30,909
Two goals, Dad.
That's what I got.

391
00:34:30,911 --> 00:34:33,178
One bounced off the pole.

392
00:34:33,180 --> 00:34:35,680
Excuse me. It's, uh... It's
time for some cleaning.

393
00:34:35,682 --> 00:34:36,914
Okay.

394
00:34:36,916 --> 00:34:38,983
I'll see you guys soon.

395
00:34:38,985 --> 00:34:41,485
Okay, bye. All right.

396
00:34:41,487 --> 00:34:43,153
Come on, guys.

397
00:34:43,155 --> 00:34:45,823
Go be with your grandparents
for a minute, okay?

398
00:34:45,825 --> 00:34:47,324
Be good boys.

399
00:34:47,326 --> 00:34:49,460
See you guys soon.

400
00:34:53,397 --> 00:34:56,132
We have the best kids
in the world.

401
00:34:58,034 --> 00:35:00,035
Yeah.

402
00:35:00,037 --> 00:35:01,771
We sure do.

403
00:35:06,543 --> 00:35:09,078
Hi. How y'all doing?

404
00:35:09,946 --> 00:35:12,079
You okay? Joe?

405
00:35:13,382 --> 00:35:15,182
Okay.

406
00:35:15,184 --> 00:35:17,345
Eva, I think the kids
should come home with us.

407
00:35:19,019 --> 00:35:20,854
We'll find a school
for 'em close by,

408
00:35:20,856 --> 00:35:24,457
and that way you won't have to worry about
if they're being taken care of or not.

409
00:35:24,459 --> 00:35:28,261
Yeah, and-and that way you can
focus fully on taking care of Don.

410
00:35:31,766 --> 00:35:33,366
Let me talk to Don first.

411
00:35:33,368 --> 00:35:35,868
I'm not sure if that's a
decision he can make right now.

412
00:35:35,870 --> 00:35:38,204
Dad. You live 250 miles away.

413
00:35:38,206 --> 00:35:40,439
We won't be able to see
them every day. I know.

414
00:35:40,441 --> 00:35:44,310
I know it's gonna be tough.
But Don needs you now.

415
00:35:45,478 --> 00:35:49,113
And we can bring the kids
back anytime you want.

416
00:35:50,549 --> 00:35:52,950
It's best if I speak with Don.

417
00:35:52,952 --> 00:35:55,453
All right. Okay.

418
00:36:01,892 --> 00:36:03,659
Hi.

419
00:36:05,262 --> 00:36:07,696
How you doing today?

420
00:36:09,932 --> 00:36:12,333
Hmm? How you feeling?

421
00:36:17,439 --> 00:36:20,241
My dad thinks
it would be better for them

422
00:36:20,243 --> 00:36:22,409
to take the kids
back to Louisiana,

423
00:36:22,411 --> 00:36:25,478
at least until we can get
you out of the hospital.

424
00:36:28,315 --> 00:36:31,584
I don't think
that's a very good idea.

425
00:36:32,919 --> 00:36:34,486
I know.

426
00:36:35,354 --> 00:36:37,422
But it'll be better for them.

427
00:36:37,424 --> 00:36:39,490
Because that way I don't
have to keep finding people

428
00:36:39,492 --> 00:36:42,359
to take them to school
and pick them up every day.

429
00:36:42,361 --> 00:36:45,930
It's not a good idea, Eva.

430
00:36:45,932 --> 00:36:49,534
It's going to be
impossible for me

431
00:36:49,536 --> 00:36:54,104
to return to teaching school
and maintain health insurance,

432
00:36:54,106 --> 00:36:58,108
spend time with you and find the
energy to take care of our children.

433
00:36:58,110 --> 00:37:00,610
No.

434
00:37:03,548 --> 00:37:05,181
Don.

435
00:37:07,351 --> 00:37:09,485
Letting my parents
take the kids

436
00:37:09,487 --> 00:37:12,754
is the only sensible
solution we have here.

437
00:37:17,726 --> 00:37:19,360
I want you to agree.

438
00:37:21,629 --> 00:37:24,897
I will find peace if we
both agree to let them go.

439
00:37:35,143 --> 00:37:37,545
I'm sending them home
with my parents.

440
00:38:28,303 --> 00:38:30,937
<i>Welcome to McDonald's.</i>
<i>Can I take your order?</i>

441
00:38:32,440 --> 00:38:35,208
Hi. Yes. We will have
two cheeseburgers,

442
00:38:35,210 --> 00:38:38,545
two shakes
and two fries, please.

443
00:38:38,547 --> 00:38:42,107
<i>Thank you. Please pull
up to the window.</i>

444
00:39:18,324 --> 00:39:20,793
<i>Until it was time</i>
<i>for me to come home,</i>

445
00:39:20,795 --> 00:39:23,028
<i>Eva would never</i>
<i>sleep in our bed.</i>

446
00:39:24,497 --> 00:39:27,166
<i>And that couch</i>
<i>was not comfortable.</i>

447
00:39:27,168 --> 00:39:29,434
<i>I know, 'cause I've been there.</i>

448
00:40:05,875 --> 00:40:08,477
Yes. Hello.
My name is Eva Piper.

449
00:40:08,479 --> 00:40:10,812
I'm looking
to hire an attorney.

450
00:40:20,657 --> 00:40:22,824
Mrs. Pepper? Piper.

451
00:40:22,826 --> 00:40:25,494
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm Cecil Beaumont.

452
00:40:25,496 --> 00:40:27,963
Pleasure. I am your Beau.

453
00:40:29,332 --> 00:40:32,768
Before we start,
can I ask you a question?

454
00:40:32,770 --> 00:40:34,336
Yes.

455
00:40:34,338 --> 00:40:36,604
How did you hear about me?

456
00:40:36,606 --> 00:40:39,541
Billboard. There was a
sign by a drive-through.

457
00:40:39,543 --> 00:40:41,976
See there? A sign.

458
00:40:45,214 --> 00:40:49,084
Something we all need in a time
of uncertainty, don't you think?

459
00:40:52,955 --> 00:40:56,191
Your husband was hit by a
state truck from the prison,

460
00:40:56,193 --> 00:40:58,193
is that right? Yes.

461
00:40:58,195 --> 00:41:00,028
Cherry.

462
00:41:01,297 --> 00:41:02,930
Driven by an inmate?

463
00:41:04,365 --> 00:41:06,866
Cherry.

464
00:41:06,868 --> 00:41:11,905
Now, it's not illegal for them
to let an inmate drive a truck.

465
00:41:11,907 --> 00:41:15,576
But it shows poor judgment on the
part of those officials at the prison

466
00:41:15,578 --> 00:41:19,614
to let an untested,
inexperienced driver

467
00:41:19,616 --> 00:41:23,883
take control of an
18-wheel tractor-trailer.

468
00:41:23,885 --> 00:41:27,654
Triple cherry!
Ka-ching! Jackpot!

469
00:41:30,824 --> 00:41:33,092
Several of my friends
are concerned

470
00:41:33,094 --> 00:41:35,928
that there might be
some kind of a cover-up

471
00:41:35,930 --> 00:41:39,131
or that the State of Texas will
try and deny who drove the truck.

472
00:41:40,333 --> 00:41:44,002
Well, your friends,
are they attorneys?

473
00:41:45,004 --> 00:41:46,637
No. Okay.

474
00:41:46,639 --> 00:41:49,774
Their legal advice is worth
what you paid for it, okay?

475
00:41:49,776 --> 00:41:53,810
There might be an attempt to alter the
circumstances surrounding the accident.

476
00:41:53,812 --> 00:41:56,413
I mean, that's more likely
what they'll do.

477
00:41:56,415 --> 00:41:58,314
Uh...

478
00:41:58,316 --> 00:42:02,419
You know, they're on the hook
for a pretty big claim here.

479
00:42:02,421 --> 00:42:07,724
So I think we can assume pretty stout
pushback from the State of Texas.

480
00:42:08,926 --> 00:42:11,427
Do we have a case?

481
00:42:11,429 --> 00:42:13,563
Excuse me.

482
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:19,201
918's Tulsa, isn't it?

483
00:42:21,170 --> 00:42:22,703
I'm sorry. Wha... You, uh...

484
00:42:22,705 --> 00:42:25,006
Did you just ask,
do we have a case?

485
00:42:25,008 --> 00:42:27,975
Ma'am, I wouldn't be here
if there wasn't a case.

486
00:42:27,977 --> 00:42:30,610
I am your Beau.

487
00:42:30,612 --> 00:42:35,848
And "mont," as in you have
