01:02:23,000 --> 01:02:27,636
There's nothing you can do
to change things?

742
01:02:27,638 --> 01:02:31,707
It's about what the hospital can
get from the insurance company.

743
01:02:31,709 --> 01:02:35,210
What about our case?
Our settlement?

744
01:02:35,212 --> 01:02:37,880
Well, I've got good news
and I've got bad news,

745
01:02:37,882 --> 01:02:42,351
but the bad news takes out the good news,
so all we're left with really is bad news.

746
01:02:42,353 --> 01:02:44,152
What?

747
01:02:44,154 --> 01:02:48,490
Well, in Texas, state employees are
indemnified by the State of Texas.

748
01:02:48,492 --> 01:02:51,793
Okay, how does this affect us?

749
01:02:51,795 --> 01:02:54,396
Well, the state,
in this case, Texas,

750
01:02:54,398 --> 01:02:59,633
has put a cap on all damages
that are able to be collected

751
01:02:59,635 --> 01:03:01,969
in any lawsuit
against the state.

752
01:03:01,971 --> 01:03:04,338
And the cap is $250,000.

753
01:03:04,340 --> 01:03:09,143
Now, insurance companies,
they have subrogation rights,

754
01:03:09,145 --> 01:03:12,080
which means that
they're gonna put a lien

755
01:03:12,082 --> 01:03:15,750
against any kind
of claim and settlement

756
01:03:15,752 --> 01:03:19,821
or any funds received from a lawsuit,
to cover their medical expenses.

757
01:03:19,823 --> 01:03:21,856
In other words,

758
01:03:21,858 --> 01:03:25,093
your insurance company
is gonna take all the money.

759
01:03:25,861 --> 01:03:27,394
Don will receive nothing?

760
01:03:28,829 --> 01:03:31,498
No. You know, I had a friend
one time, he asked me.

761
01:03:31,500 --> 01:03:36,837
He said, "What kind of cookies you
bake when you don't have any money?"

762
01:03:36,839 --> 01:03:40,440
I said, "I don't know. What?"
He said, "Shortbread."

763
01:03:40,442 --> 01:03:43,577
Unfortunately, Don's gonna have to
bake shortbread cookies on this one.

764
01:03:43,579 --> 01:03:47,447
He'd been better off if he'd
been hit by a Budweiser truck.

765
01:03:47,449 --> 01:03:51,785
And then we'd all be talking
about millions of dollars.

766
01:03:53,754 --> 01:03:57,891
Sorry. Partner,
can I give you that card?

767
01:03:57,893 --> 01:04:02,028
You show up here
just to tell me this?

768
01:04:02,030 --> 01:04:03,896
<i>How we gonna do this?</i>

769
01:04:03,898 --> 01:04:07,834
We'll take him by ambulance.
You can drive your car.

770
01:04:12,307 --> 01:04:16,076
<i>Even though St. Luke's was</i>
<i>only five blocks away,</i>

771
01:04:16,078 --> 01:04:20,714
<i>it was such a painful move with
the fixators on my leg and arm.</i>

772
01:04:20,716 --> 01:04:24,218
<i>Every bump resonated</i>
<i>through my bones.</i>

773
01:04:27,555 --> 01:04:29,222
<i>Eva stayed strong,</i>

774
01:04:29,224 --> 01:04:32,426
<i>tried not to cry out as she</i>
<i>watched me go through this.</i>

775
01:04:32,428 --> 01:04:36,297
It's not very pretty here.

776
01:04:39,401 --> 01:04:41,682
It's not ideal. I'm sorry.

777
01:04:46,609 --> 01:04:48,844
I'm so sorry, Don.

778
01:04:58,588 --> 01:05:03,526
When they picked this color blue,
it must have been a cloudy day.

779
01:05:09,366 --> 01:05:12,986
Mr. Piper, Mrs. Piper, how
you guys doing today?

780
01:05:13,012 --> 01:05:14,537
Hi there. Thank you.

781
01:05:14,539 --> 01:05:18,808
Good, good. I've got some
relief for you, Mr. Piper.

782
01:05:18,810 --> 01:05:22,811
I'm gonna take good care of you, okay?
Let me just have that arm.

783
01:05:22,813 --> 01:05:27,282
I'm gonna just
hook this up for you,

784
01:05:27,284 --> 01:05:29,525
and this will make you
feel a lot better.

785
01:05:34,823 --> 01:05:36,791
All righty.

786
01:05:36,793 --> 01:05:39,493
This is real simple, Mr. Piper.

787
01:05:39,495 --> 01:05:42,196
All you need to do is...

788
01:05:45,667 --> 01:05:49,370
Anytime you feel
you need some relief,

789
01:05:50,905 --> 01:05:54,375
this will just
take it all away for you.

790
01:05:54,377 --> 01:05:56,810
All I need you to do is push
this little button here,

791
01:05:56,812 --> 01:05:59,646
and it releases medication.

792
01:05:59,648 --> 01:06:02,349
All right?

793
01:06:02,351 --> 01:06:05,318
And just call me if you need me.
All right, Mrs. Piper?

794
01:06:05,320 --> 01:06:07,921
- Thank you.
- All right. You're welcome.

795
01:06:19,234 --> 01:06:22,603
Mr. Piper and Mrs. Piper,
how you doing today?

796
01:06:22,605 --> 01:06:24,672
We're fine, thank you. Good.

797
01:06:24,674 --> 01:06:27,541
And how about him?

798
01:06:27,543 --> 01:06:29,342
Hey, Mr. Piper.

799
01:06:30,211 --> 01:06:33,546
So, have you eaten today?

800
01:06:33,548 --> 01:06:35,581
Hmm?

801
01:06:35,583 --> 01:06:37,617
Did you have therapy today?

802
01:06:39,019 --> 01:06:41,788
Did Dr. Greider come by?

803
01:06:43,892 --> 01:06:47,660
Have you had
a bowel movement today?

804
01:06:48,895 --> 01:06:50,595
Maybe that's why
you're so grumpy.

805
01:06:52,698 --> 01:06:55,534
All right, I'll be back
later to check up on you.

806
01:06:55,536 --> 01:06:59,070
Just let me know if I can get
you anything. Thank you.

807
01:06:59,072 --> 01:07:00,605
You're welcome.

808
01:07:15,155 --> 01:07:17,122
Why don't you talk?

809
01:07:20,560 --> 01:07:23,881
I can't figure out what's
going on inside of you.

810
01:07:28,167 --> 01:07:30,169
What happened to you?

811
01:07:35,507 --> 01:07:38,076
Talk to me.

812
01:07:38,078 --> 01:07:41,680
Don, answer me.

813
01:07:43,416 --> 01:07:48,187
I'm sitting right here. Please.
Why aren't you answering me?

814
01:07:52,925 --> 01:07:55,160
Where do you go?

815
01:07:59,264 --> 01:08:01,733
You're not even here anymore.

816
01:08:10,443 --> 01:08:13,179
Is there something
you want to tell me?

817
01:08:17,885 --> 01:08:20,453
Where's my husband?

818
01:08:25,059 --> 01:08:27,226
He's not here.

819
01:08:39,473 --> 01:08:41,506
I miss him.

820
01:08:45,145 --> 01:08:48,147
Should I get that for you?

821
01:08:48,149 --> 01:08:50,229
Should I answer that for you?

822
01:08:55,388 --> 01:08:57,522
Hello?

823
01:08:57,524 --> 01:09:00,359
How's Don?

824
01:09:00,361 --> 01:09:05,597
He doesn't talk, he lies here,
and he doesn't seem to care.

825
01:09:07,266 --> 01:09:10,067
- Hi, Dad.
- Let me call you back. Okay.

826
01:09:10,069 --> 01:09:11,669
What's that?

827
01:09:11,671 --> 01:09:15,172
<i>I know I should have been</i>
<i>grateful to be alive.</i>

828
01:09:15,174 --> 01:09:19,076
<i>My downcast attitude was</i>
<i>taking its toll on everyone.</i>

829
01:09:19,078 --> 01:09:22,345
<i>But I just felt like</i>
<i>something was missing</i>

830
01:09:22,347 --> 01:09:25,082
<i>and I didn't deserve to be here.
</i> Hi, Daddy.

831
01:09:29,687 --> 01:09:33,256
Okay, kids, it's time to get on the road.
We need to not tire out your father.

832
01:09:33,258 --> 01:09:36,260
It's okay, Dad. I'm gonna take them
on the first floor to the McDonald's.

833
01:09:36,262 --> 01:09:38,461
Come on. Come on, baby.
Come on.

834
01:09:41,431 --> 01:09:45,701
Are you okay, Mom?

835
01:09:45,703 --> 01:09:47,269
Yeah.

836
01:09:49,873 --> 01:09:53,153
I never would have dreamed that
cheeseburger and fries would be so good.

837
01:09:58,047 --> 01:09:59,748
I'm in love with french fries.

838
01:09:59,750 --> 01:10:03,051
You're in love
with french fries?

839
01:10:03,053 --> 01:10:04,652
Me too.

840
01:10:09,324 --> 01:10:11,826
Do you think Dad will be home
for my birthday?

841
01:10:14,496 --> 01:10:19,500
I hope so. I know he wants to.

842
01:10:19,502 --> 01:10:23,270
Grandpa, um,
makes us do our homework

843
01:10:23,272 --> 01:10:26,240
<i>before</i> we go to the lake.

844
01:10:26,242 --> 01:10:28,942
As he should.

845
01:10:28,944 --> 01:10:31,178
But he doesn't help us
like you do.

846
01:10:54,037 --> 01:10:58,673
Don, I came to say good night.

847
01:11:02,045 --> 01:11:04,413
You don't want to say
good night?

848
01:11:09,119 --> 01:11:12,722
I am tired of this.

849
01:11:16,326 --> 01:11:18,695
You don't seem to care
about anything.

850
01:11:20,564 --> 01:11:23,533
You don't care that
you're back here with us.

851
01:11:27,137 --> 01:11:30,540
You don't care when the children
come and visit you.

852
01:11:35,312 --> 01:11:37,614
You don't want to grow old
with me?

853
01:11:41,151 --> 01:11:43,385
Or see the children
get married?

854
01:11:46,021 --> 01:11:47,789
You don't care.

855
01:11:53,763 --> 01:11:56,664
You can take your pain away
with that button,

856
01:11:56,666 --> 01:12:00,402
but you are causing it
to everyone else.

857
01:12:34,771 --> 01:12:38,107
<i>Welcome to McDonald's.</i>
<i>Can I take your order?</i>

858
01:13:22,417 --> 01:13:26,253
<i>Sorry. That's not on the menu.</i>

859
01:13:38,767 --> 01:13:40,400
Lord.

860
01:13:44,705 --> 01:13:47,507
Oh, God...

861
01:13:50,177 --> 01:13:52,678
Does it really
have to be like this?

862
01:14:00,188 --> 01:14:04,823
The pain... of the injuries,

863
01:14:04,825 --> 01:14:06,725
I can handle that.

864
01:14:11,898 --> 01:14:14,966
Even seeing the pity

865
01:14:14,968 --> 01:14:19,871
and the helplessness in the
eyes of the people who love me

866
01:14:19,873 --> 01:14:22,406
and care for me...

867
01:14:23,141 --> 01:14:25,710
I can get through that.

868
01:14:32,484 --> 01:14:35,118
But if this is as good
as it's ever gonna get,

869
01:14:42,194 --> 01:14:44,127
I don't wanna be a burden.

870
01:14:45,329 --> 01:14:47,664
I was just trying
to get back to Alvin,

871
01:14:47,666 --> 01:14:49,966
and you took me to heaven.

872
01:14:53,036 --> 01:14:55,571
Why can't you take me back?

873
01:15:00,877 --> 01:15:02,577
Now.

874
01:15:09,085 --> 01:15:11,019
I wanna go back to heaven,

875
01:15:15,024 --> 01:15:17,526
my home.

876
01:15:21,029 --> 01:15:23,598
My home is heaven now.

877
01:15:26,401 --> 01:15:29,703
Oh, Jesus, let me
come back home, please.

878
01:15:36,644 --> 01:15:39,478
Please let me come back home.

879
01:16:14,849 --> 01:16:18,785
Well, South Park hired me
to be your interim

880
01:16:18,787 --> 01:16:21,020
while you're, uh,
incapacitated,

881
01:16:21,022 --> 01:16:23,890
so I guess you can say
I'm out of retirement.

882
01:16:27,261 --> 01:16:30,197
Uh, can I get you a magazine?

883
01:16:34,468 --> 01:16:37,204
Would-Would you like a...
a milk shake?

884
01:16:41,008 --> 01:16:44,845
How about a hamburger? You lost
quite a bit of weight, son.

885
01:16:51,453 --> 01:16:54,456
Would you like for me to

886
01:16:54,458 --> 01:16:57,559
read to you from the Bible?

887
01:16:57,561 --> 01:16:59,361
Or any other book,
for that matter?

888
01:16:59,363 --> 01:17:03,331
Really, no.

889
01:17:03,333 --> 01:17:05,967
Thanks for coming.

890
01:17:15,043 --> 01:17:17,364
You know, you really need
to get your act together.

891
01:17:21,149 --> 01:17:24,018
Sir? You need to get
your act together.

892
01:17:24,020 --> 01:17:26,720
You're not doing
a very good job right now.

893
01:17:27,822 --> 01:17:29,990
Uh, I'm not sure I understand.

894
01:17:29,992 --> 01:17:34,894
Besides that,
you're a raging hypocrite.

895
01:17:34,896 --> 01:17:37,831
I don't know what
you're talking...

896
01:17:37,833 --> 01:17:41,669
You got all these people
out there

897
01:17:41,671 --> 01:17:45,005
who care so much for you, and you
have no idea how much they love you.

898
01:17:45,007 --> 01:17:46,673
I know they love me.
Oh, really?

899
01:17:46,675 --> 01:17:49,076
Yeah. Well, you're doing
a pretty poor job

900
01:17:49,078 --> 01:17:51,178
of letting them know
you're aware of that fact.

901
01:17:51,180 --> 01:17:52,946
I don't think you're treating
them right.

902
01:17:52,948 --> 01:17:57,851
Now, they can't heal you, but they
would heal you if they could.

903
01:18:00,021 --> 01:18:02,922
And if they could trade places with
you, many of them would do that.

904
01:18:02,924 --> 01:18:03,618
Yeah...

905
01:18:03,644 --> 01:18:06,393
And do anything for
you without any waver.

906
01:18:06,395 --> 01:18:08,315
I don't want them
to do anything.

907
01:18:12,867 --> 01:18:15,034
Truth is, I don't even
want them to be here.

908
01:18:15,036 --> 01:18:17,636
I'd just as soon they not come.

909
01:18:19,238 --> 01:18:20,805
I-I-I know it's inconvenient.

910
01:18:20,807 --> 01:18:23,875
They must have better things to do.
I know that.

911
01:18:23,877 --> 01:18:27,878
Why would I want anyone
to come see me like this?

912
01:18:27,880 --> 01:18:29,747
Huh?

913
01:18:29,749 --> 01:18:33,650
It's awful.

914
01:18:36,321 --> 01:18:38,221
It's not your call.

915
01:18:38,223 --> 01:18:41,725
It's not about you.

916
01:18:41,727 --> 01:18:46,095
You spent the better part of your life
trying to minister to other people.

917
01:18:46,097 --> 01:18:48,731
Trying to be there
for their needs.

918
01:18:48,733 --> 01:18:52,267
And to be there for them
through difficulty and tragedy.

919
01:18:52,269 --> 01:18:53,902
I-I've tried to.

920
01:18:53,904 --> 01:18:59,774
And yet you have deprived them
of doing the same thing for you.

921
01:18:59,776 --> 01:19:02,342
And that's all they have
to offer you, Don.

922
01:19:04,144 --> 01:19:07,514
And you're taking that gift
away from them.

923
01:19:07,516 --> 01:19:11,085
I appreciate them. I do.

924
01:19:11,087 --> 01:19:14,455
I-I know they want to help, and I
think that's very fine and all,

925
01:19:14,457 --> 01:19:16,417
but... But nothing!

926
01:19:20,861 --> 01:19:24,030
Now, I want you to let
them in, you hear me?

927
01:19:24,032 --> 01:19:29,035
You're going to let them in
and let 'em help you.

928
01:19:29,037 --> 01:19:30,936
I can't.

929
01:19:34,307 --> 01:19:37,909
Well, if you don't feel
like you can for yourself,

930
01:19:39,378 --> 01:19:41,699
what about doing it for me?

931
01:19:44,884 --> 01:19:48,187
What about next time somebody walks through
that door and wants to do something for you...

932
01:19:48,189 --> 01:19:51,690
I don't care what it is...
say yes.

933
01:19:51,692 --> 01:19:57,830
Let a few folks express their
love by doing something for you.

934
01:19:57,832 --> 01:20:00,633
I mean, promise me
that you'll do that.

935
01:20:00,635 --> 01:20:02,568
Just...

936
01:20:02,570 --> 01:20:06,739
Look, just try it for me.

937
01:20:09,142 --> 01:20:12,044
You're gonna need
to get better at this.

938
01:20:12,046 --> 01:20:14,880
Now, this is one of the lessons
that God wants you to learn.

939
01:20:18,651 --> 01:20:20,385
All right, I promise.

940
01:20:24,256 --> 01:20:27,992
People are God's hands

941
01:20:27,994 --> 01:20:32,397
to meet your needs
and answer your prayers.

942
01:20:38,371 --> 01:20:41,107
We'll just keep looking
till it feels right.

943
01:20:41,109 --> 01:20:44,076
What kind of house
are we looking for?

944
01:20:44,078 --> 01:20:48,881
Well, probably something
one-story.

945
01:20:48,883 --> 01:20:52,618
Manageable to get around in
for Dad.

946
01:20:52,620 --> 01:20:57,356
Is Dad gonna be in a wheelchair?
Yeah.

947
01:20:57,358 --> 01:20:59,058
For a little while.

948
01:20:59,060 --> 01:21:01,393
<i>As the medical bills</i>
<i>were mounting,</i>

949
01:21:01,395 --> 01:21:04,596
<i>Eva looked for a house</i>
<i>that we could afford,</i>

950
01:21:04,598 --> 01:21:08,299
<i>that would accommodate my needs once
I was discharged from St. Luke's.</i>

951
01:21:10,402 --> 01:21:12,704
Hey, hey, hey. There he is.

952
01:21:12,706 --> 01:21:15,173
Got something for you.

953
01:21:20,380 --> 01:21:23,815
Look, let me do it.
Looks like you need my help.

954
01:21:23,817 --> 01:21:26,918
How are you today?

955
01:21:26,920 --> 01:21:29,421
Not speaking to me again?

956
01:21:29,423 --> 01:21:32,891
Hmm. Okay. It's a letter.

957
01:21:32,893 --> 01:21:35,060
It says, "Hi, there.
We share wrenches."

958
01:21:35,062 --> 01:21:38,496
Fortunately for both of us, our
fixators are interchangeable.

959
01:21:38,498 --> 01:21:42,133
"And we can borrow tools from
one another." That's so cute.

960
01:21:42,135 --> 01:21:44,235
Look it there.
It's a happy face.

961
01:21:44,237 --> 01:21:47,439
Who is this?
Oh, this is from Christy.

962
01:21:47,441 --> 01:21:50,241
Christy is a teenage girl
that lives in the next room.

963
01:21:50,243 --> 01:21:52,911
She was born with one leg
shorter than the other.

964
01:21:52,913 --> 01:21:57,147
So she had to have surgery to attach
the Ilizarov frame, like yours,

965
01:21:57,149 --> 01:21:59,016
so that both legs
would be of normal size.

966
01:21:59,018 --> 01:22:02,285
She has a fixator too?
She goes on.

967
01:22:02,287 --> 01:22:05,622
"And we share
something else too. Pain."

968
01:22:05,624 --> 01:22:09,258
She says, "I hear you scream at night
sometimes as you probably hear me too."

969
01:22:09,260 --> 01:22:14,464
Although our nurse says
that you don't admit to it."

970
01:22:14,466 --> 01:22:18,769
Don't-Don't-Don't shoot me now. I'm
just the messenger, Mr. Piper.

971
01:22:18,771 --> 01:22:23,320
And she goes on and says,
"You're not alone.

972
01:22:23,346 --> 01:22:25,443
Sincerely, Christy."

973
01:22:25,445 --> 01:22:28,546
That is so sweet.

974
01:22:28,548 --> 01:22:31,882
Can you get me a pen
and paper, please?

975
01:22:33,150 --> 01:22:36,119
I can if you acknowledge me.

976
01:22:36,121 --> 01:22:40,489
There you go.

977
01:22:40,491 --> 01:22:43,292
I like that. All right.

978
01:22:43,294 --> 01:22:45,860
I'll be right back.
That's my boy.

979
01:22:48,631 --> 01:22:54,169
<i>Dear Christy, in some of my
worst moments of self-pity,</i>

980
01:22:54,171 --> 01:22:57,172
<i>I think of never</i>
<i>being normal again.</i>

981
01:22:57,174 --> 01:23:01,009
<i>I believe that when all of
the pain is over, Christy,</i>

982
01:23:01,011 --> 01:23:03,144
<i>you will be</i>
<i>a normal young woman.</i>

983
01:23:03,146 --> 01:23:07,848
<i>You will play and run and do</i>
<i>everything a normal teen can do.</i>

984
01:23:07,850 --> 01:23:12,753
<i>You're doing something that positively
impacts the rest of your life.</i>

985
01:23:12,755 --> 01:23:16,924
<i>Keep the faith. Kindest, Don.</i>

986
01:23:17,992 --> 01:23:21,760
<i>If God brings you to it,</i>

987
01:23:21,762 --> 01:23:23,395
<i>he will bring you through it.</i>

988
01:23:40,078 --> 01:23:41,845
It's not long
before you go home.

989
01:23:41,847 --> 01:23:44,681
This is your first step
in that direction.

990
01:23:52,289 --> 01:23:55,025
My first step
is wanting to vomit.

991
01:23:55,027 --> 01:23:57,260
Yeah, nausea will get you
every time.

992
01:23:57,262 --> 01:23:59,730
Your equilibrium has changed.

993
01:23:59,732 --> 01:24:02,699
You've grown used to being
in a horizontal position.

994
01:24:02,701 --> 01:24:04,534
I'd like my tools back.

995
01:24:06,070 --> 01:24:09,138
Hi. I'm Christy,
your long-lost pen pal.

996
01:24:09,140 --> 01:24:12,041
Or Hopalong Cassidy,
as my friends say.

997
01:24:12,043 --> 01:24:16,111
Hi. I'm Don.

998
01:24:17,814 --> 01:24:21,315
How are you? Could be worse.

999
01:24:21,317 --> 01:24:23,584
How's that?

1000
01:24:23,586 --> 01:24:26,119
Okay, you got me.
It can't get much worse.

1001
01:24:26,121 --> 01:24:30,557
The endless reruns OO AM?

1002
01:24:32,393 --> 01:24:35,396
Yeah, well,
I wish my only problem

1003
01:24:35,398 --> 01:24:38,031
was getting hit in the face
with a football like Marcia.

1004
01:24:39,433 --> 01:24:42,369
I'd take a broken nose
to dance normal.

1005
01:24:45,506 --> 01:24:47,307
You'll dance.

1006
01:24:52,078 --> 01:24:54,884
Only the truest friends show
up when you have to move.

1007
01:24:54,910 --> 01:24:56,414
Trust me, this is a vacation.

1008
01:24:56,416 --> 01:24:59,084
Oh, vacation?
Yes, from my children.

1009
01:24:59,086 --> 01:25:02,754
Ah, well, thank you.

1010
01:25:02,756 --> 01:25:05,615
Remember when Don's parents
gave us this painting?

1011
01:25:05,641 --> 01:25:06,792
Oh, yes, I remember.

1012
01:25:06,794 --> 01:25:10,495
I remember you tried to pawn it
off on me, and then Susan,

1013
01:25:10,497 --> 01:25:13,098
and the Goodwill store.
That's not true!

1014
01:25:13,100 --> 01:25:15,266
That is true. I never told Don.

1015
01:25:19,373 --> 01:25:23,109
Is all this stuff going to fit
in the new house? I think so.

1016
01:25:23,111 --> 01:25:24,710
This place just isn't
gonna work for Don.

1017
01:25:24,712 --> 01:25:27,612
You know, with all the stairs
and him being in a wheelchair.

1018
01:25:27,614 --> 01:25:30,782
Plus, the new home
is closer to the church.

1019
01:25:30,784 --> 01:25:33,284
That will be nice.

1020
01:25:37,356 --> 01:25:40,992
Just came by to check on you,
see how you were doing.

1021
01:25:40,994 --> 01:25:45,996
You're looking good. I hear you're
gonna be going home before long.

1022
01:25:45,998 --> 01:25:48,699
Anything I can do for you
before I go?

1023
01:25:48,701 --> 01:25:51,802
That-That's a very fine offer.

1024
01:25:51,804 --> 01:25:54,305
Um...

1025
01:25:54,307 --> 01:25:57,741
- I wish I had a magazine to read.
- You do?

1026
01:25:57,743 --> 01:26:01,811
Really? I think so.

1027
01:26:01,813 --> 01:26:03,712
I-I haven't read one
in a while.

1028
01:26:05,148 --> 01:26:07,382
Well, all right.
Give me just a minute.

1029
01:26:07,384 --> 01:26:10,853
<i>Jay B. Perkins,</i>
<i>a retired minister,</i>

1030
01:26:10,855 --> 01:26:12,988
<i>was a powerful</i>
<i>father figure to me.</i>

1031
01:26:12,990 --> 01:26:17,159
<i>And I was grateful for his service to
my church while I was incapacitated.</i>

1032
01:26:17,161 --> 01:26:18,760
This ought to do you.

1033
01:26:20,028 --> 01:26:22,229
There you go.
Th-Th-Thank you much.

1034
01:26:22,231 --> 01:26:24,432
That'll keep you busy.
I'll read them a bit later.

1035
01:26:24,434 --> 01:26:26,700
Yeah. Anything else I can do?

1036
01:26:26,702 --> 01:26:29,770
No, that's... that's all I need.
Thank you.

1037
01:26:29,772 --> 01:26:31,438
You know,
when you open the door

1038
01:26:31,440 --> 01:26:35,409
and let somebody do
something nice for you,

1039
01:26:35,411 --> 01:26:38,244
it turns out not to be
so hard after all, huh?

1040
01:26:39,079 --> 01:26:40,680
You were right, J.B.

1041
01:26:42,282 --> 01:26:47,620
I thought that relieving people
of the responsibility

1042
01:26:47,622 --> 01:26:51,190
of having to care for me
was the right thing to do.

1043
01:26:53,961 --> 01:26:56,095
It wasn't.

1044
01:26:57,630 --> 01:27:01,367
They would heal me if they could,
and since they can't do that,

1045
01:27:01,369 --> 01:27:05,538
they were caring for me in...
in the only way that they can.

1046
01:27:08,074 --> 01:27:12,211
I have denied them the...

1047
01:27:12,213 --> 01:27:15,080
the blessing of caring.

1048
01:27:15,082 --> 01:27:18,283
You've loved me enough
to tell me the truth.

1049
01:27:19,218 --> 01:27:21,118
I won't forget it.

1050
01:27:27,993 --> 01:27:30,295
<i>And I never have.</i>

1051
01:27:34,566 --> 01:27:39,403
<i>After 34 surgeries and nearly
four months in the hospital,</i>

1052
01:27:39,405 --> 01:27:42,106
<i>Dr. Greider said</i>
<i>I could go home.</i>

1053
01:27:42,108 --> 01:27:43,674
Bye. Thank you.

1054
01:27:44,809 --> 01:27:48,245
Dr. Greider. Hold up a sec.

1055
01:27:49,747 --> 01:27:52,115
Tell me something.

1056
01:27:52,117 --> 01:27:55,785
Just how bad was I when they brought
me in the night of the accident?

1057
01:27:55,787 --> 01:27:57,353
I've seen worse.

1058
01:27:58,254 --> 01:28:00,489
But they didn't live.

1059
01:28:03,526 --> 01:28:04,927
Thank you, sir.

1060
01:28:04,929 --> 01:28:07,162
<i>He would become a friend of
mine from that day forward.</i>

1061
01:28:07,164 --> 01:28:08,863
Bye, Christy. Bye.

1062
01:28:08,865 --> 01:28:11,726
I want you to call me
when you get out of here.

1063
01:28:11,752 --> 01:28:12,525
Will do.

1064
01:28:38,229 --> 01:28:41,198
- Hi, Daddy!
- Hey, Dad.

1065
01:28:42,300 --> 01:28:44,634
How do you like the new house?

1066
01:28:45,969 --> 01:28:50,072
What do you think? Welcome home, Daddy.
Welcome home.

1067
01:28:50,074 --> 01:28:53,910
- I think I'm home.
- There's the kitchen.

1068
01:28:53,912 --> 01:28:56,879
Did you put milk in it?
I'm just gonna do this.

1069
01:29:04,588 --> 01:29:08,990
I know. Is it good? Mm-hmm.

1070
01:29:08,992 --> 01:29:12,160
Smells good in there.

1071
01:29:14,664 --> 01:29:18,266
Why don't you... We're gonna play a game.
Okay, you ready?

1072
01:29:20,502 --> 01:29:23,905
<i>Eva organized something</i>
<i>called "The Don Patrol,"</i>

1073
01:29:23,907 --> 01:29:26,374
<i>a group of church members and
friends who took care of me</i>

1074
01:29:26,376 --> 01:29:30,845
<i>so that she could teach</i>
<i>and we could keep our insurance.</i>

1075
01:29:30,847 --> 01:29:34,916
<i>The Don Patrol would arrive around
9:00 while I was still sleeping.</i>

1076
01:29:36,885 --> 01:29:38,452
Good morning.

1077
01:29:38,454 --> 01:29:40,454
<i>I might awake to seeing</i>
<i>one of the Susans</i>

1078
01:29:40,456 --> 01:29:42,690
<i>knitting on the couch</i>
<i>at the end of my bed.</i>

1079
01:29:43,925 --> 01:29:45,892
<i>Or someone would be there</i>
<i>with a toothbrush</i>

1080
01:29:45,894 --> 01:29:48,762
- <i> so I could brush my teeth.</i>
- Looking good.

1081
01:29:48,764 --> 01:29:52,600
<i>Oftentimes holding a glass of juice
before I was done doing that.</i>

1082
01:29:52,602 --> 01:29:55,536
<i>Maybe even offering</i>
<i>an electric shaver.</i>

1083
01:29:55,538 --> 01:30:00,041
All right, I've never actually
used one of these before.

1084
01:30:00,043 --> 01:30:01,709
It's pretty simple.

1085
01:30:03,878 --> 01:30:06,380
You know what?
It doesn't actually work.

1086
01:30:06,382 --> 01:30:08,382
<i>And a big lunch.</i>

1087
01:30:08,384 --> 01:30:13,320
Turkey sandwich,
oatmeal cookie, pickles.

1088
01:30:13,322 --> 01:30:15,388
You can't pass up baby pickles.

1089
01:30:15,390 --> 01:30:16,990
I'll take the apple. Okay.

1090
01:30:16,992 --> 01:30:21,260
Another friend might be reading the
newspaper, ready to entertain me.

1091
01:30:21,262 --> 01:30:23,763
Yeah, whatever you need.

1092
01:30:23,765 --> 01:30:25,798
I'll even sing for you
if you want.

1093
01:30:25,800 --> 01:30:29,702
Some guests would even make
themselves quite comfortable.

1094
01:30:34,941 --> 01:30:36,441
Hey, Butterfly.

1095
01:30:36,443 --> 01:30:39,844
Come here.

1096
01:30:39,846 --> 01:30:41,513
Butterfly.

1097
01:30:41,515 --> 01:30:44,415
No!

1098
01:30:44,417 --> 01:30:45,849
Butterfly, no!

1099
01:30:46,818 --> 01:30:48,318
Hey!

1100
01:30:51,121 --> 01:30:55,024
Hi, honey. Everything okay?

1101
01:30:55,026 --> 01:30:56,658
Uh-huh.

1102
01:30:58,260 --> 01:31:00,829
You sure? Yeah.

1103
01:31:04,501 --> 01:31:09,671
It smells like pee in here.
I know. It was the dog.

1104
01:31:11,508 --> 01:31:14,276
It's okay if you can't make it
to the bathroom.

1105
01:31:14,278 --> 01:31:18,447
It was the dog.

1106
01:31:19,282 --> 01:31:20,715
Butterfly?

1107
01:31:28,792 --> 01:31:30,893
Hey, Dad.

1108
01:32:32,127 --> 01:32:33,727
Come on.

1109
01:32:33,729 --> 01:32:35,763
You can do it.

1110
01:32:55,252 --> 01:32:55,752
Aaah!

1111
01:32:59,390 --> 01:33:03,891
I did it.

1112
01:33:09,397 --> 01:33:12,065
I did it.

1113
01:33:13,400 --> 01:33:17,069
I walked!

1114
01:33:17,071 --> 01:33:19,071
I walked.

1115
01:33:19,073 --> 01:33:22,140
Oh, Lord, I walked.

1116
01:33:34,989 --> 01:33:38,658
- What's going on?
- What's happening?

1117
01:33:38,660 --> 01:33:41,261
Ma'am. Ma'am. Where Don?
Where's my husband?

1118
01:33:41,263 --> 01:33:45,031
Ma'am. I'd like for you to
consider this as a private matter.

1119
01:33:45,033 --> 01:33:46,165
Private? Private.

1120
01:33:46,167 --> 01:33:48,768
This is my house. I've seen it all.
Hey.

1121
01:33:48,770 --> 01:33:51,837
- Bet you haven't seen this yet.
- What's going on?

1122
01:33:55,108 --> 01:33:59,011
I, uh, got my fixator
stuck to the toilet seat.

1123
01:33:59,013 --> 01:34:00,112
Oh.

1124
01:34:00,114 --> 01:34:03,148
Happy birthday!

1125
01:34:11,691 --> 01:34:16,895
This is a perfect day. God has given me
children so much better than I deserve.

1126
01:34:16,897 --> 01:34:21,032
How can I ever thank you
for all they mean to me?

1127
01:34:26,839 --> 01:34:29,808
You being alive is the gift.

1128
01:34:33,313 --> 01:34:35,080
Dad, will you dance with me?

1129
01:34:35,981 --> 01:34:37,748
Ah, sweetie, I'd like to, but...

1130
01:34:37,750 --> 01:34:41,085
Please, Dad. Please?
I don't think I can.

1131
01:34:54,830 --> 01:34:57,130
I might need you
to help me up here.

1132
01:35:34,937 --> 01:35:39,472
David! What are you doing here?

1133
01:35:39,474 --> 01:35:41,708
I'm in town for
a discipleship weekend.

1134
01:35:41,710 --> 01:35:44,210
It's the excuse I use

1135
01:35:44,212 --> 01:35:47,914
to come into the house
and spend time with you.

1136
01:35:47,916 --> 01:35:51,217
Thank you for your friendship.

1137
01:35:51,219 --> 01:35:56,555
And your relentless
commitment to prayer.

1138
01:35:56,557 --> 01:35:58,598
Of course, Don.
How you feeling now?

1139
01:35:59,459 --> 01:36:03,929
In pain.
But I'm always in pain.

1140
01:36:03,931 --> 01:36:07,199
That's... That's not the worst
part of it for me right now.

1141
01:36:09,835 --> 01:36:14,372
There are things I can't
physically do anymore.

1142
01:36:24,016 --> 01:36:28,253
I'm not sure that God wants me
to continue at South Park.

1143
01:36:28,255 --> 01:36:33,324
I feel loved and needed there, but
I'm not sure it's where I should be.

1144
01:36:38,196 --> 01:36:42,733
What did you learn from y-your
accident and your recovery experience?

1145
01:36:44,836 --> 01:36:47,038
Letting other people inside.

1146
01:36:48,340 --> 01:36:50,307
Allowing others to help me.

1147
01:36:50,309 --> 01:36:55,379
But in the midst of all
the suffering and despondency,

1148
01:36:57,215 --> 01:36:58,716
David,

1149
01:37:02,619 --> 01:37:05,688
I've learned
that heaven is real.

1150
01:37:07,991 --> 01:37:11,694
- What do you mean by that?
- I died that day.

1151
01:37:16,533 --> 01:37:20,903
The next moment
I stood in heaven.

1152
01:37:28,213 --> 01:37:30,981
Why haven't you
mentioned this before?

1153
01:37:30,983 --> 01:37:35,019
I have two very good
reasons for that.

1154
01:37:35,021 --> 01:37:37,688
Number one, I go around talking
about having been to heaven,

1155
01:37:37,690 --> 01:37:40,224
and people will think I'm nuts.

1156
01:37:40,226 --> 01:37:42,159
Why would you think that?
You just told me.

1157
01:37:42,161 --> 01:37:43,660
- Number two...
- I don't think you're nuts.

1158
01:37:43,662 --> 01:37:45,863
Number two, I don't wanna go
over that experience again.

1159
01:37:49,166 --> 01:37:52,735
It's too personal, too special.

1160
01:37:52,737 --> 01:37:54,837
It's my sacred secret.

1161
01:37:56,606 --> 01:38:00,509
Is it possible
that God took you to heaven,

1162
01:38:00,511 --> 01:38:05,747
brought you back so that you could
share your experience with others?

1163
01:38:05,749 --> 01:38:10,485
Don't you realize what a powerful
encouragement you could be?

1164
01:38:13,021 --> 01:38:16,124
I want you to make
a covenant with me.

1165
01:38:16,126 --> 01:38:18,960
What kind of a covenant?
It's simple.

1166
01:38:18,962 --> 01:38:21,228
Find someone you trust.

1167
01:38:21,230 --> 01:38:24,432
Share a little bit about your story
just to gauge their response.

1168
01:38:24,434 --> 01:38:27,468
If they think you're crazy
or you hallucinated,

1169
01:38:27,470 --> 01:38:32,440
I promise, I promise you never
have to talk about it again.

1170
01:38:35,545 --> 01:38:37,546
But if they rejoice with you

1171
01:38:37,548 --> 01:38:42,051
and urge you to tell them more,
I want you to take it as a sign.

1172
01:38:42,053 --> 01:38:46,322
A sign that God wants you to talk about
those 90 minutes you spent in heaven.

1173
01:38:50,226 --> 01:38:54,329
- I think I can do that much.
- When?

1174
01:38:54,331 --> 01:38:58,666
Soon. I promise.
Very soon, right?

1175
01:38:58,668 --> 01:39:01,368
All right. Very soon.

1176
01:39:06,575 --> 01:39:09,243
Hi, honey. Hi, darlin'.

1177
01:39:09,245 --> 01:39:12,947
Hey, David.
Glad you could make it.

1178
01:39:12,949 --> 01:39:15,082
Soon as in now.

1179
01:39:25,494 --> 01:39:27,495
Honey? Yes.

1180
01:39:34,938 --> 01:39:39,341
Darlin', I want to tell you something.
What's that?

1181
01:39:44,114 --> 01:39:48,017
Remember the day I-I left
for the convention? Uh-huh.

1182
01:39:48,019 --> 01:39:52,621
Well, that morning just plays
over and over in my head.

1183
01:39:52,623 --> 01:39:55,857
And you said, "I.O.U."

1184
01:39:57,292 --> 01:39:58,960
Yes. And I do.

1185
01:40:01,063 --> 01:40:03,864
Well, in fact,
I think I owe<i> you.</i>

1186
01:40:03,866 --> 01:40:08,268
Oh, don't I know it. I've been
waiting a long time for that.

1187
01:40:10,805 --> 01:40:13,139
I owe you an explanation.

1188
01:40:14,975 --> 01:40:17,110
Darlin', would you sit down
for a second?

1189
01:40:18,145 --> 01:40:19,545
Please.

1190
01:40:34,730 --> 01:40:36,397
You know,
I died in that accident.

1191
01:40:42,037 --> 01:40:43,904
When I woke up,

1192
01:40:45,339 --> 01:40:47,140
I was in heaven.

1193
01:40:51,778 --> 01:40:53,346
You went to heaven?

1194
01:40:56,549 --> 01:40:58,284
Yes.

1195
01:41:00,587 --> 01:41:02,287
Tell me more.

1196
01:41:07,693 --> 01:41:10,128
When I died,

1197
01:41:10,130 --> 01:41:13,631
I didn't flow through
a long dark tunnel.

1198
01:41:13,633 --> 01:41:15,065
Uh...

1199
01:41:15,067 --> 01:41:18,202
I had no sense of fading away
or coming back.

1200
01:41:18,204 --> 01:41:21,003
I heard no voices calling to
me or anything like that.

1201
01:41:23,607 --> 01:41:29,278
Simultaneous with my last
recollection of seeing the bridge,

1202
01:41:29,280 --> 01:41:31,112
<i>the rain,</i>

1203
01:41:33,950 --> 01:41:37,052
<i>a light enveloped me,</i>

1204
01:41:37,054 --> 01:41:39,254
<i>with a brilliance</i>

1205
01:41:39,256 --> 01:41:43,225
<i>beyond earthly comprehension</i>
<i>or description.</i>

1206
01:41:46,563 --> 01:41:52,568
<i>In my next moment of awareness,</i>
<i>I was standing in heaven.</i>

1207
01:41:52,570 --> 01:41:54,736
<i>It was perfect.</i>

1208
01:41:54,738 --> 01:41:59,274
<i>And I knew right then I would have
no needs and never would again.</i>

1209
01:41:59,276 --> 01:42:04,246
<i>I didn't even think of Earth</i>
<i>or of those left behind.</i>

1210
01:42:04,248 --> 01:42:07,349
<i>Though I did not see Jesus</i>
<i>face-to-face,</i>

1211
01:42:07,351 --> 01:42:10,419
<i>I did sense his presence</i>
<i>at every turn.</i>

1212
01:42:10,421 --> 01:42:12,754
<i>And I did see people</i>
<i>I had known.</i>

1213
01:42:12,756 --> 01:42:15,323
<i>As they surged towards me,</i>

1214
01:42:15,325 --> 01:42:19,360
<i>I knew instantly that all of them
had died during my lifetime.</i>

1215
01:42:19,362 --> 01:42:23,765
<i>Their presence</i>
<i>seemed absolutely natural.</i>

1216
01:42:23,767 --> 01:42:29,471
<i>It was as if God had removed anything
negative or worrisome from my consciousness.</i>

1217
01:42:29,473 --> 01:42:33,274
<i>And I could only rejoice at being
together with these wonderful people.</i>

1218
01:42:33,276 --> 01:42:38,013
Donnie, I'm so excited
you're here to join us.

1219
01:42:41,684 --> 01:42:44,218
<i>I saw Papa.</i>

1220
01:42:44,220 --> 01:42:47,388
<i>You know, my grandfather</i>
<i>that everyone called Joe.</i>

1221
01:42:47,390 --> 01:42:51,893
<i>I heard his voice</i>
<i>and felt his embrace.</i>

1222
01:42:51,895 --> 01:42:54,896
<i>I'd been with him when he'd</i>
<i>suffered a heart attack at home</i>

1223
01:42:54,898 --> 01:42:57,966
<i>and had ridden with him</i>
<i>in the ambulance.</i>

1224
01:42:57,968 --> 01:43:01,135
<i>I'd been standing just outside the
emergency room at the hospital</i>

1225
01:43:01,137 --> 01:43:04,172
<i>when the doctor walked out</i>
<i>and faced me.</i>

1226
01:43:04,174 --> 01:43:07,008
<i>The doctor shook his head</i>
<i>and said softly,</i>

1227
01:43:07,010 --> 01:43:09,243
<i>"We did everything we could."</i>

1228
01:43:10,980 --> 01:43:13,381
<i>As I walked among them,</i>

1229
01:43:13,383 --> 01:43:16,651
<i>I became aware</i>
<i>of the wide variety of ages.</i>

1230
01:43:16,653 --> 01:43:20,488
<i>Old and young</i>
<i>and every age in between.</i>

1231
01:43:20,490 --> 01:43:23,158
<i>Many of them hadn't known each</i>
<i>other on Earth,</i>

1232
01:43:23,160 --> 01:43:27,361
<i>but each had influenced</i>
<i>my life in some way.</i>

1233
01:43:27,363 --> 01:43:30,031
<i>Even though they</i>
<i>hadn't met on Earth,</i>

1234
01:43:30,033 --> 01:43:33,267
<i>they seemed to know</i>
<i>each other now.</i>

1235
01:43:33,269 --> 01:43:36,170
<i>One person in the greeting</i>
<i>committee was Mike Wood,</i>

1236
01:43:36,172 --> 01:43:38,505
<i>my childhood friend.</i>

1237
01:43:38,507 --> 01:43:41,008
<i>He was a popular kid</i>
<i>and became a hero to me</i>

1238
01:43:41,010 --> 01:43:46,013
<i>because he lived the Christian
lifestyle and often talked about it.</i>

1239
01:43:46,015 --> 01:43:51,617
<i>After high school, Mike received a full
scholarship to Louisiana State University.</i>

1240
01:43:51,619 --> 01:43:56,021
<i>When he was 19,</i>
<i>Mike was killed in a car wreck.</i>

1241
01:43:56,023 --> 01:44:00,559
<i>When I attended his funeral, I
wondered if I would ever stop crying.</i>

1242
01:44:00,561 --> 01:44:05,530
<i>I couldn't understand why God had
taken such a dedicated disciple.</i>

1243
01:44:05,532 --> 01:44:11,203
<i>Through the years since then, I had never been
able to forget that pain and sense of loss.</i>

1244
01:44:11,205 --> 01:44:13,972
<i>Then I saw Barry Wilson,</i>

1245
01:44:13,974 --> 01:44:17,676
<i>who had been classmate in high
school, but later drowned in a lake.</i>

1246
01:44:19,378 --> 01:44:23,781
<i>Barry's smile radiated a happiness
I didn't know was possible.</i>

1247
01:44:26,151 --> 01:44:29,787
<i>And I saw my great-grandmother</i>
<i>Hattie Mann.</i>

1248
01:44:29,789 --> 01:44:33,825
<i>As a child, I knew her only after
she had developed osteoporosis.</i>

1249
01:44:33,827 --> 01:44:36,561
<i>Her head and her shoulders</i>
<i>were always bent forward,</i>

1250
01:44:36,563 --> 01:44:39,798
<i>giving her a...</i>
<i>a sort of humped appearance.</i>

1251
01:44:39,800 --> 01:44:45,470
<i>But the beautiful thing is, she
didn't carry these burdens in heaven.</i>

1252
01:44:45,472 --> 01:44:49,241
<i>Heaven was many things,</i>
<i>but without a doubt,</i>

1253
01:44:49,243 --> 01:44:53,145
<i>it was the greatest</i>
<i>family reunion of all.</i>

1254
01:44:57,583 --> 01:45:00,819
<i>A holy awe came over me</i>
<i>as I stepped forward.</i>

1255
01:45:01,821 --> 01:45:04,089
<i>I had no idea what lay ahead.</i>

1256
01:45:04,091 --> 01:45:08,226
<i>But I sensed that with each step I
took, it would grow more wondrous.</i>

1257
01:45:09,862 --> 01:45:12,430
<i>Then I heard the music.</i>

1258
01:45:12,432 --> 01:45:16,668
<i>I can only describe it</i>
<i>as a holy swoosh of wings.</i>

1259
01:45:16,670 --> 01:45:19,137
<i>But I'd have to magnify that</i>
<i>thousands of times</i>

1260
01:45:19,139 --> 01:45:22,441
<i>to explain the effect</i>
<i>of the sound in heaven.</i>

1261
01:45:22,443 --> 01:45:26,711
<i>It was the most beautiful and</i>
<i>pleasant sound I'd ever heard.</i>

1262
01:45:28,181 --> 01:45:30,782
<i>I saw a bright iridescence.</i>

1263
01:45:30,784 --> 01:45:35,020
<i>I peered through the gate,</i>
<i>yearning to see what lay beyond.</i>

1264
01:45:35,022 --> 01:45:37,322
<i>It wasn't an anxious</i>
<i>yearning, but,</i>

1265
01:45:37,324 --> 01:45:39,324
<i>uh, a peaceful openness</i>

1266
01:45:39,326 --> 01:45:43,895
<i>to experience all of the
grace and joy of heaven.</i>

1267
01:45:43,897 --> 01:45:49,000
<i>At that very moment I was about to realize
the yearning of every human heart.</i>

1268
01:45:49,002 --> 01:45:53,705
<i>I was in heaven and ready to go
through the pearlescent gates.</i>

1269
01:45:57,042 --> 01:46:01,812
<i>Then, just as suddenly as I'd arrived
at the gates of heaven, I left there.</i>

1270
01:46:04,650 --> 01:46:06,517
I spent a lot of time
in the hospital

1271
01:46:06,519 --> 01:46:09,988
trying to make sense
of all of this.

1272
01:46:09,990 --> 01:46:14,725
I was paralyzed by the notion
of not wanting to return.

1273
01:46:14,727 --> 01:46:16,929
I mean, why come back
to this much pain?

1274
01:46:21,867 --> 01:46:23,733
I think now I know.

1275
01:46:25,702 --> 01:46:27,904
I do too.

1276
01:46:32,241 --> 01:46:35,276
I believe it's time for me
to go back to church.

1277
01:46:37,412 --> 01:46:39,446
I believe that too.

1278
01:46:42,350 --> 01:46:44,917
Have you told anyone else
about this?

1279
01:46:49,690 --> 01:46:52,625
Yes. David.

1280
01:46:54,527 --> 01:46:56,828
Are you hurt that I
didn't tell you first?

1281
01:47:01,200 --> 01:47:02,633
No.

1282
01:47:03,736 --> 01:47:06,704
I feel elated to know,

1283
01:47:06,706 --> 01:47:10,775
because it enables me to understand
the man to whom I'm married.

1284
01:47:14,212 --> 01:47:16,980
- Eva.
- Yes?

1285
01:47:19,216 --> 01:47:20,816
Eva.

1286
01:47:20,818 --> 01:47:26,322
No one should have to do the
things that you had to do for me.

1287
01:47:26,324 --> 01:47:28,792
But you did them,

1288
01:47:28,794 --> 01:47:31,895
faithfully, compassionately
and without hesitation.

1289
01:47:38,969 --> 01:47:43,106
You come closest to really
knowing how painful

1290
01:47:43,108 --> 01:47:45,307
this journey has been for me.

1291
01:47:47,411 --> 01:47:51,748
Each day you endured it with me.

1292
01:47:58,322 --> 01:48:02,325
Eva, you are my gift from God.

1293
01:48:13,272 --> 01:48:17,876
<i>I was so enthusiastic about
finally returning to South Park.</i>

1294
01:48:17,878 --> 01:48:21,145
<i>I hadn't been out of bed for</i>
<i>more than an hour at a time and,</i>

1295
01:48:21,147 --> 01:48:25,550
<i>well, I overestimated my endurance and
suddenly felt incredibly fatigued.</i>

1296
01:48:27,787 --> 01:48:32,624
<i>Yet, the... the overwhelming response
from the congregation gave me</i>

1297
01:48:32,626 --> 01:48:34,393
<i>a new burst of strength,</i>

1298
01:48:34,395 --> 01:48:38,663
<i>and I knew right then that their praise
was for God's work and my healing.</i>

1299
01:48:38,665 --> 01:48:44,169
It's only taken me...
five months

1300
01:48:44,171 --> 01:48:47,373
to get from the conference at
Trinity Pines back to church?

1301
01:48:50,143 --> 01:48:53,746
I may be slow, but I'm faithful.

1302
01:49:00,021 --> 01:49:03,088
They would like for you to say
something to the congregation.

1303
01:49:03,090 --> 01:49:05,991
Eva, I think I made a mistake.
I don't think I can do this.

1304
01:49:05,993 --> 01:49:08,059
You can.
I'm not sure if I'm ready.

1305
01:49:08,061 --> 01:49:10,128
You are.

1306
01:49:16,769 --> 01:49:19,604
Let's hear it, Don.

1307
01:49:19,606 --> 01:49:23,075
Say something, Don, please.

1308
01:49:58,216 --> 01:49:59,816
You prayed.

1309
01:50:03,954 --> 01:50:06,121
I'm here.

1310
01:50:19,402 --> 01:50:21,403
Oh, there he is. Hey, Don!

1311
01:50:21,405 --> 01:50:23,139
Don!

1312
01:50:24,441 --> 01:50:28,611
Hey! You made it. Yeah.

1313
01:50:28,613 --> 01:50:31,180
It's so good to see you.

1314
01:50:31,182 --> 01:50:35,919
I believe that I'm alive today
because you prayed me back to Earth.

1315
01:50:35,921 --> 01:50:38,521
Tell you what. You buy me
lunch, we'll call it even.

1316
01:50:38,523 --> 01:50:40,257
All right, it's a deal.

1317
01:50:40,259 --> 01:50:41,191
That's right.

1318
01:50:42,326 --> 01:50:44,160
I couldn't figure out
how to get inside,

1319
01:50:44,162 --> 01:50:46,796
so I just pried open the trunk,

1320
01:50:46,798 --> 01:50:49,465
knocked down the backseat
and crawled in that way.

1321
01:50:49,467 --> 01:50:52,168
But even when I was praying with
you, I didn't know it was you.

1322
01:50:52,170 --> 01:50:55,337
Besides, no one lives through that.
Hmm.

1323
01:50:55,339 --> 01:51:00,742
Well, in my first moments of
consciousness, two things stand out.

1324
01:51:01,944 --> 01:51:07,115
First, I was singing.

1325
01:51:07,117 --> 01:51:10,285
I don't sing. No.

1326
01:51:10,287 --> 01:51:13,321
"What a Friend
We Have in Jesus."

1327
01:51:13,323 --> 01:51:16,858
And the second was that Dick had
climbed into the car with me,

1328
01:51:16,860 --> 01:51:20,994
and... and his hand had gripped
mine and held it tight.

1329
01:51:20,996 --> 01:51:23,797
But the one thing
that is absolutely clear

1330
01:51:23,799 --> 01:51:26,299
was Dick being in the car
and praying with me.

1331
01:51:26,301 --> 01:51:31,004
That's true. He did get in
the car and prayed with you.

1332
01:51:31,006 --> 01:51:34,141
But, Don,
he never held your hand.

1333
01:51:37,912 --> 01:51:41,015
- Nope.
- I-I remember it so clearly though.

1334
01:51:41,017 --> 01:51:45,987
It was one of the most
vivid details.

1335
01:51:45,989 --> 01:51:50,191
- It didn't happen.
- It was physically impossible.

1336
01:51:50,193 --> 01:51:54,829
There's just no physical way possible
I could have reached your right hand.

1337
01:51:57,700 --> 01:52:01,268
But...

1338
01:52:01,270 --> 01:52:03,236
But I-I-I swear, I...

1339
01:52:03,238 --> 01:52:05,606
Someone was holding your hand.

1340
01:52:06,507 --> 01:52:09,175
But it wasn't Dick.

1341
01:52:09,177 --> 01:52:14,414
<i>Dick Onerecker was a real prayer
warrior before and after the accident.</i>

1342
01:52:14,416 --> 01:52:18,685
<i>He would pass away only a few years
after praying for me on that bridge.</i>

1343
01:52:27,128 --> 01:52:29,163
Okay, you guys, right in here.

1344
01:52:48,552 --> 01:52:51,220
- Hey, darlin'.
- Yeah. Mm-hmm?

1345
01:52:51,222 --> 01:52:53,156
I'll be right back. Okay.

1346
01:53:11,744 --> 01:53:15,179
Boy, that really hurts,
doesn't it?

1347
01:53:15,181 --> 01:53:19,083
Yeah, it hurts very much.
Yeah, I know.

1348
01:53:22,755 --> 01:53:27,625
Believe me, I know. You do?

1349
01:53:27,627 --> 01:53:30,327
Yeah. I had one too.

1350
01:53:34,099 --> 01:53:35,766
It's horrible.

1351
01:53:35,768 --> 01:53:38,602
Ah, it's... it's just horrible.

1352
01:53:38,604 --> 01:53:41,772
It's awful. I know that.

1353
01:53:41,774 --> 01:53:45,275
I wore one on my left leg
for 11 months.

1354
01:53:45,277 --> 01:53:48,312
Nobody ever understands.
Well, they can't.

1355
01:53:48,314 --> 01:53:53,116
It's not something you can talk about
and have anyone understand your pain.

1356
01:53:54,818 --> 01:53:56,852
I'm Don. Mark.

1357
01:53:57,788 --> 01:53:59,722
Well, Mark,

1358
01:53:59,724 --> 01:54:03,693
you just met someone
who does understand the pain

1359
01:54:03,695 --> 01:54:08,196
and the discouragement
you're going through.

1360
01:54:09,500 --> 01:54:13,935
I don't know if I'm gonna make it.
Oh, you'll make it.

1361
01:54:14,970 --> 01:54:17,405
You're gonna make it. Hey.

1362
01:54:17,407 --> 01:54:20,307
Hey, trust me. You'll make it.

1363
01:54:23,345 --> 01:54:25,679
What happened?

1364
01:54:25,681 --> 01:54:27,815
I had a skiing accident.

1365
01:54:30,552 --> 01:54:33,988
- You're a football player?
- Yes, sir.

1366
01:54:35,490 --> 01:54:37,824
I'm gonna tell you something.

1367
01:54:37,826 --> 01:54:42,862
One day, you will walk again.

1368
01:54:42,864 --> 01:54:46,106
Might not be playing
football, but you'll walk.

1369
01:54:47,000 --> 01:54:49,201
Here's my card.
Number's right there.

1370
01:54:49,203 --> 01:54:52,972
You can call me anytime, day or
night, 24 hours a day. All right?

1371
01:54:56,109 --> 01:55:00,546
Now, I'm gonna walk back
over there to my family.

1372
01:55:00,548 --> 01:55:03,416
I want you to watch me,

1373
01:55:03,418 --> 01:55:07,953
and as you watch, I want you to do
know that one day you will walk too.

1374
01:55:12,959 --> 01:55:15,160
You'll probably do it
better than I do.

1375
01:55:18,532 --> 01:55:22,935
You met someone who understands.
Give me a call, all right?

1376
01:55:22,937 --> 01:55:26,438
Thank you. Thank you.
Thank you so much.

1377
01:55:26,440 --> 01:55:30,309
Hey, it's not about me.

1378
01:55:30,311 --> 01:55:35,648
<i>Before I died on that bridge, I was
unsure of what my purpose was.</i>

1379
01:55:35,650 --> 01:55:37,916
<i>Now I see it more clearly.</i>

1380
01:55:37,918 --> 01:55:40,653
<i>Ministering and sharing</i>
<i>the hope I found.</i>

1381
01:56:06,915 --> 01:56:11,584
Over 25 years ago,
that big truck

1382
01:56:11,586 --> 01:56:15,688
took my life
on that old bridge.

1383
01:56:15,690 --> 01:56:21,159
I am not the man I used to be.

1384
01:56:21,161 --> 01:56:26,998
I have been beaten up,
but I'm not beaten.

1385
01:56:27,000 --> 01:56:31,503
I have chosen to be

1386
01:56:31,505 --> 01:56:34,507
not bitter, but better.

1387
01:56:34,509 --> 01:56:38,043
And it<i> is</i> a choice.

1388
01:56:39,212 --> 01:56:43,315
Every day of my life,
I still ask the same question

1389
01:56:43,317 --> 01:56:48,354
that I asked in that bed,
that hospital bed, every day.

1390
01:56:49,622 --> 01:56:52,691
Oh, Lord, why?

1391
01:56:52,693 --> 01:56:58,030
Why did you let me see heaven
and take it away from me?

1392
01:57:01,134 --> 01:57:06,805
I believe it is so that
I could be here with<i> you</i> today

1393
01:57:06,807 --> 01:57:09,307
and tell you to your face,

1394
01:57:11,643 --> 01:57:15,880
God still answers prayer.

1395
01:57:15,882 --> 01:57:19,483
God is still in
the miracle business today.

1396
01:57:19,485 --> 01:57:25,022
God is able to help us
find a new normal

1397
01:57:25,024 --> 01:57:29,493
and overcome tragedy and loss,
pain and suffering.

1398
01:57:31,896 --> 01:57:35,832
And God is building us
a better place.

1399
01:57:35,834 --> 01:57:39,269
Heaven is real.

1400
01:57:42,006 --> 01:57:46,610
I may not meet you here,
this side of heaven.

1401
01:57:48,679 --> 01:57:52,015
So my prayer for you today is,

1402
01:57:52,017 --> 01:57:56,252
if I don't meet you<i> here,</i>
one day,

1403
01:57:56,254 --> 01:58:01,357
I want to see you<i> there</i>
at the gates.

1404
01:58:03,728 --> 01:58:05,762
And may God help us

1405
01:58:05,764 --> 01:58:09,933
to be found faithful
until that day.

